concept_explanation.frequency_array:
**int[26] frequency array — fastest for lowercase alpha:**

```java
// Anagram check:
bool isAnagram(String s, String t) {
    if(s.length()!=t.length()) return false;
    int[] freq = new int[26];
    for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++) {
        freq[s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
        freq[t.charAt(i)-'a']--;
    }
    for(int f:freq) if(f!=0) return false;
    return true; // O(n) time, O(1) space
}

// Group anagrams key:
// Sort chars → canonical form: 'eat','tea','ate' all → 'aet'
// Or use frequency tuple: [1,0,0,...,1,0,...] (26 values)
```

concept_explanation.sliding_window_anagram:
**Find all anagrams — fixed window + int[26]:**

```java
// Fixed window of size p.length()
// Compare int[26] arrays: O(26) = O(1) per slide
int[] need=new int[26], have=new int[26];
for(char c:p.toCharArray()) need[c-'a']++;
for(int i=0;i<p.length();i++) have[s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
if(Arrays.equals(need,have)) result.add(0);
for(int i=p.length();i<s.length();i++) {
    have[s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
    have[s.charAt(i-p.length())-'a']--;
    if(Arrays.equals(need,have)) result.add(i-p.length()+1);
}
```
